                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>There is evidence of two inscriptions on the stone. The first inscription is on two angles of the stone and reads upwards, across the top and then down. According to Macalister, the first inscription which is given as ...]LL MAQI VORRTIGURN is a secondary inscription. The older inscription on the stone which is given as DIOBI reads upwards was apparently copied <q>in minute pin-scrapes on the unoccupied part of the second inscribed angle</q> (Macalister 1945, 93). </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>Macalister described the inscription's minute scores as <q>like rather straggling <rs type="execution" key="scratched" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/9.html">knife-cuts</rs></q> (1945, 93).<height></height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
